remove.packages             package:utils              R Documentation

_R_e_m_o_v_e _I_n_s_t_a_l_l_e_d _P_a_c_k_a_g_e_s

_D_e_s_c_r_i_p_t_i_o_n:

     Removes installed packages/bundles and updates index information
     as necessary.

_U_s_a_g_e:

     remove.packages(pkgs, lib)
     
_A_r_g_u_m_e_n_t_s:

    pkgs: a character vector with the names of the packages to be
          removed.

     lib: a character vector giving the library directories to remove
          the packages from.  If missing, defaults to the first element
          in ‘.libPaths()’.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o:

     On Unix-alikes, ‘REMOVE’ for a command line version;

     ‘install.packages’ for installing packages.


